EXTRACTED VALUE: Apart from exciting moments that are few and far between, the game is dull and uninspiring.
Every aspect that "works" has a few that just don't, to the game's overall detriment.
The excellent control scheme and shiny units aren’t enough to save UAW from its own flawed code.
MvA doesn’t do anything wrong per se, it’s just not the game that’s going to bring new fans over to the sport of motocross.
